    Oracle checks:
      ⊨ sentiment ∈ {"positive", "negative", "mixed"} ✓
      ⊨ confidence ∈ [0, 100] ✓
      ⊨ text has positive and negative → sentiment = "mixed" ✓

    All oracles pass. Attempt 2 accepted.

Step 2: generate-response
  Inputs: sentiment ≡ "mixed", confidence ≡ 84

  Attempt 1:
    generate-response → response ≡ "Thank you for sharing your thoughts!
      We're glad you find our product innovative and love the design.
      We hear your concerns about pricing and battery life and are
      actively working on improvements in both areas.",
      tone ≡ "empathetic"

    Oracle checks:
      ⊨ tone = "empathetic" if sentiment = "mixed" ✓
      ⊨ response mentions specific concerns ("pricing", "battery life") ✓

    All oracles pass. Attempt 1 accepted.

Step 3: quality-gate
  Inputs: response ≡ ..., tone ≡ "empathetic", sentiment ≡ "mixed"

  ⊢= approved ← (tone = "empathetic" ∧ sentiment ∈ {"negative", "mixed"})
    = ("empathetic" = "empathetic" ∧ "mixed" ∈ {"negative", "mixed"})
    = (true ∧ true)
    = true

  yield approved ≡ true, reason ≡ ∅

